    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but sitting in the dark doesn't change the fact that the house is still collapsing. it's just a slow way to wait for the end. why does everyone keep pushing the \"it gets better\" thing when you can literally feel yourself disintegrating? it feels like people are just afraid to admit that sometimes, things are just done. that there's no point in carrying the weight anymore.",
